## 🟠 HIGH: Logging Security - No Sensitive Data

**NEVER log sensitive information:**

- ❌ `console.log(args.iparams)` → May contain API keys, tokens, passwords
- ❌ `console.log(args)` in handlers → May expose entire request including secrets
- ❌ `console.log('Auth:', authToken)` → Exposes credentials
- ❌ `console.error(e)` with full error objects → May leak sensitive context

### Forbidden Logging Patterns:

```javascript
// ❌ SECURITY RISK - Logs all iparams including API keys
onAppInstallHandler: async function(args) {
  console.log('App installed', args.iparams);
}

// ❌ SECURITY RISK - Logs entire args object
onTicketCreateHandler: async function(args) {
  console.log('Ticket created', args);
}
```

### Safe Logging Patterns:

```javascript
// ✅ SAFE - Log only confirmation, no sensitive data
onAppInstallHandler: async function(args) {
  console.log('App installed successfully');
}

// ✅ SAFE - Log only non-sensitive, specific fields
onTicketCreateHandler: async function(args) {
  console.log('Ticket created:', args.data?.ticket?.id);
}

// ✅ SAFE - Sanitized error logging
catch (e) {
  console.error('Operation failed:', e.message);
}
```

### Logging Security Checklist:
- [ ] Never log `args.iparams` directly
- [ ] Never log full `args` objects in handlers
- [ ] Never log tokens, passwords, API keys, or secrets
- [ ] Log only operation status and non-sensitive identifiers
- [ ] Sanitize error messages before logging

