## 🟡 MEDIUM: Sensitive Data Handling

**NEVER store sensitive data in visible/accessible locations:**

- ❌ Passwords in ticket notes or comments
- ❌ API keys in ticket custom fields
- ❌ Secrets displayed in UI without masking
- ❌ Credentials stored in browser localStorage

### Forbidden Patterns:

```javascript
// ❌ SECURITY RISK - Password visible in ticket notes
const note = 'Password: ' + generatedPassword;
await client.interface.trigger('addNote', { content: note });

// ❌ SECURITY RISK - Secret in localStorage
localStorage.setItem('apiKey', apiKey);
```

### Safe Patterns:

```javascript
// ✅ SAFE - Send password via secure channel only
await client.request.invoke('sendSecureEmail', {
  to: requesterEmail,
  password: generatedPassword,
  expiresIn: '24h'
});
await client.interface.trigger('addNote', {
  content: 'Temporary password sent to requester email. Expires in 24h.',
  isPrivate: true
});

// ✅ SAFE - Use server-side storage for secrets
await $db.set('integration_token', { token: encryptedToken });
```

### Sensitive Data Checklist:
- [ ] Never store passwords/secrets in ticket notes
- [ ] Never display full credentials in UI
- [ ] Use secure delivery mechanisms (email with expiry)
- [ ] Store secrets server-side using $db or encrypted storage
- [ ] Mask sensitive data in logs and displays

