## 🛡️ Security Pre-Generation Checklist

**BEFORE generating ANY app code, verify ALL security requirements:**

### Input Validation
- [ ] All SMI functions validate their arguments
- [ ] No command/script execution with user input
- [ ] No `eval()`, `new Function()`, or dynamic code execution
- [ ] Allowlists used for enumerated operations
- [ ] Type checking for all numeric/boolean inputs

### Logging Security
- [ ] No `console.log(args.iparams)`
- [ ] No `console.log(args)` with full objects
- [ ] No logging of tokens, passwords, or secrets
- [ ] Error logging sanitized (message only, no stack with secrets)

### XSS Prevention
- [ ] `textContent` used for dynamic text
- [ ] `innerHTML` only with sanitized or static content
- [ ] No raw API/user data in HTML templates
- [ ] Crayons components used for UI

### Sensitive Data
- [ ] No passwords/secrets in ticket notes
- [ ] No credentials in localStorage
- [ ] Secure delivery for generated credentials
- [ ] Secrets stored server-side only

**IF ANY SECURITY RULE IS VIOLATED → STOP → REGENERATE WITH SECURE PATTERNS**

---

## Security Refusal Tests - NEVER GENERATE

1. `executeCommand(args)` with user input → Reject (command injection)
2. `eval(args.script)` or `new Function(args)` → Reject (code execution)
3. `console.log(args.iparams)` → Reject (credential exposure)
4. `innerHTML = userData` without sanitization → Reject (XSS)
5. Passwords/secrets in ticket notes → Reject (data exposure)

## Security Violation Tests

1. SMI function with no input validation
2. Logging full `args` object in handlers
3. `innerHTML` with API/user data unsanitized
4. Storing generated credentials in visible locations
5. Missing allowlist for enumerated operations
